# App listing automation (agent-owned)

The user must **never** be asked to run `register-app`, `create-app`, or manual listing commands for:

- Store legal hub: `personal-site` (Vercel)
- Portfolio works list: `ymd-portfolio` (Cloudflare Pages)

## When this applies

Creating a new app, deploying a Web app, preparing App Store / Play submission, or adding something to the portfolio.

## What you must do (you, the agent)

1. Register store hub entry in `personal-site` (`tools/register-app.mjs` or `tools/publish-app-listing.mjs`).
2. If a public Web URL exists, also register portfolio (`ymd-portfolio/scripts/register-app.mjs`) with `--url`.
3. Commit and push the affected repo(s).
4. Deploy or rely on CI (Vercel auto / Cloudflare Pages workflow). Trigger `gh workflow run` / `repository_dispatch` if the listing must refresh immediately.
5. Confirm the live URLs yourself.

## Do not

- Tell the user “run this npm command to register”.
- Leave registration as a follow-up for the user.
- Confuse the portfolio (https://ymd-portfolio-site.pages.dev/) with the store legal hub (https://personal-site-taupe-gamma.vercel.app/).
